      "evidence": [
        "R2 running-config: \"Cisco-IOS-XE-ethernet:speed\": { \"value-100\": [ null ] }, \"Cisco-IOS-XE-ethernet:duplex\": \"half\", \"Cisco-IOS-XE-ethernet:negotiation\": { \"auto\": false } (call_I0zMlKkbm9xyzlTXKQP9cZfX).",
        "R1 running-config: GigabitEthernet0/0/1 \"Cisco-IOS-XE-ethernet:negotiation\": { \"auto\": true } (call_DMAWt7eypvR6DPUUWutRCSn3).",
        "Interface operational facts: router1 GigabitEthernet0/0/1 input_errors 94, output_errors 0 (get_interface_status:call_IQSPJhf6Vm420ipuYRHzGJaw).",
        "Interface operational facts: router2 GigabitEthernet0/0/1 input_errors 92, output_errors 0 (get_interface_status:call_bnroDfsv6uhQKVQ83Ox1W4jE).",
        "Both interfaces are up with speed reported as 102400000 (100Mbps) while duplex is not reported by the status probe (suggesting one side forced, the other negotiated): get_interface_status outputs for both interfaces."
